The same procedure as in Example 1 â†’ Example 3 â†’ Example 4 was carried out, except that 4-methoxycarbonyl-benzylbromide was used in place of ethyl chloroacetate in Example 1, the title compound having the following physical properties was obtained. TLC: Rf 0.1 (chloroform : methanol : 28% ammonia water = 80 : 10 : 1);

 NMR(CD
        3OD): Î´ -2.21(s, 3H), 2.88(s, 6H), 3.73(s, 2H), 3.86(s, 2H), 5.41(s, 2H), 6.98(t, J = 1.8Hz, 1H), 7.03(d, J = 1.8Hz, 1H), 7.15(d, J = 8.4Hz, 2H), 7.17(t, J = 1.8Hz, 1H), 7.45(d, J = 1.8Hz, 1H), 7.94(d, J = 8.4Hz, 2H).

